inn1.comm: what a fantastic ball! An inswinging yorker which is far, far too good for Trescothick, swinging right into him. It comes off both pads and crashes right into the stumps. A beauty and Trescothick's walking off already. Thanks for coming
a misfield at a wideish mid-off and the batsmen scamper through a single to loud cheers from the packed house
well bowled, full, and the batsman just digs that out, showing the full face of his bat

oooh, a good attempted yorker but that's well played - very well played - by Strauss who clips it off his toes and it races away through square. Then again that was bowled at 90mph and it's a good outfield so it's bound to fly
tickled into the covers and the batsmen hasten a single
short and Bell pulls out of that one at the last minute as the ball bends away from his outside edge on the up
Asif drifts into bowl, pitches that on a perfect length and Strauss is forced to play a forward defensive
very wide, although near the outside edge, but that's the right decision
full but down the legside and that's played easily behind square
pitches on a length, nips back and there's a big shout for that one, but from the bowler only and the umpire's not interested
sails down the off-side channel, the batsman leaves it alone
a touch shorter, the batsman plays an unconvincing defensive off the back foot and that gets a thick inside edge which falls harmlessly in front of him
a forward defensive this time and that's another dot. A tidy over
short and down leg and that's whipped easily off the legs but Asif races round from long leg and slides on to that one, cannoning it back in
Shoaib comes wider of the crease and that's just left alone
left alone again
once more Bell shoulders arms as a ball on a good length sails wide of the off stump
Bell reaches out to try to late cut a looser delivery at 90mph but the balls flies off the outside edge and races away down through the slips
full and that's cover-driven straight to... cover of course
well bowled, just drops on a good length and that's defended on the front foot
stock delivery, hits the seam and nips away from the lefthander
Strauss comes down the pitch and squeezes that out behind point
short and on the legs and that's easily guided out to square where it's rushed back in
lovely shot, waited for that one which pitches wide outside the off stump and Bell crashes a lovely cut through point

Strauss thinks about chasing that one, pulls out of the shot and that's called wide to cheers from the England fans - they'll cheer any run right now, it seemds, although it's a little soon to be panicking of course... it's not such a bad start
fuller and flicked away with consummate timing through square leg. Scorcher
banged in, short, wide and Bell plays a lovely backfoot cut. The outfield isn't that quick on reflection, it looks a little bit stodgy out there
paddled right round to a wide long leg
short and wide again and Bell leans into a cover-drive but finds the fielder
slower ball, picked, and that's worked into midwicket where it's easily collected by the fielder who just bends down to meet it
hostile from Shoaib, coming wide of the crease again, and that's a good ball, pitching on off and nipping right back in off the seam at the righthander
tries a similar delivery, but strays down leg this time and that's squirted into the legside for a quick single
forced on to the back foot to defend a tidy short ball
guided out into the cover region, the fielder hurries round to scoop it and wing it back in
full ball and that's defended on the front foot

comes down the pitch, plants his front foot to the pitch of the ball and clips that through midwicket, watching the ball all the way through the legside. He's been playing some very elegant legside shots today and that one is right up there
dabbed down behind square
hair flapping in the breeze and a determined expression on his face, Asif ganders in and plants the ball on a decent length, with the batsman defending that comfortably in the end
the batsmen look for a single as that drops a touch wide and it's half-driven into silly mid-off
ooh! Great delivery, squaring up Strauss a treat as that one rises and just to say misses his outside edge as it flies through to the keeper
good area to bowl to Strauss, inviting the drive and a big outside edge flies a touch aerially off the bottom of the bat and on towards third man
Bell leaps on to his back foot, and gets into position early to play a defence with the full face - and he holds that pose
pings that one in on the off-stump line and that's solidly defended
that's rushed past the outside edge as Strauss shapes to defend on the back foot. He nods his head to acknowledge the ball, as if to say, "Fair enough"
on a decent length, Strauss looks to work that one into midwicket this time but without any real power
top shot. Strauss shuffles down the pitch and merely swats that with the bottom of his blade away through gully. Nice
comes down the pitch again, thinking about looking for a single and sets off for a few steps before rushing back to his mark - there was never a run there
the bowler pushes that one right up and Strauss can only drive powerlessly to cover. Good bowling
right on the money and the batsman digs it out with a front-foot defensive
squared up by a short one but lands bat on ball which flies down without danger into the slip region
looks to drive that through cover
"waiting there," comes the call as Strauss helps that to the man at cover and so the batsmen duly wait there
clipped strongly, and with good timing, off the legs and that runs through square
full toss and that's dispatched with an unconvincing, though powerful, drive through third man, after the batsman opens the face. The ball beats the third man
helped off the legs this time.
pitched right up there and that's solidly defended. Good ball
defended off the back foot this time
not a proper bouncer and Bell was quickly on to that one, pulling it high and wide
played off his legs behind square
that's pushed up there and Strauss defends it
comes out to meet that one and he misses it completely but is back in his crease before Akmal can even think of a stumping opportunity
outside off, big swing and a miss
confidently driven through extra cover off the front foot, Yousuf caught the ball inches in from the rope
again overpitched and driven through the same spot with more timing and this time the chase was to no avail
better line and nothing that time
short and on leg stump, swatted behind square but straight to the one man there
wide outside off and cut just to the right of a diving cover. A good over for England with nine coming off it
dropped into the off side, no more than a couple of yards from the batsman, and a well-run and comfortable single
angled into Strauss and he was too cramped to be able to do anything other than defend

a stride down the track and hammered straight back from where it came ... into Bell's chest and he goes down like he has been struck by Mike Tyson. Strauss, good team man that  he is, finds the whole thing amusing until he realises that Bell is in some distress
again driven, but straighter and with less power
edged into his body and the ball plops inches from the crease and Bell calls Strauss for a quick single ...Mohammad Asif aims a kick and Bell would have been worried had he connected properly
clipped through midwicket, well placed and two with no alarms
punched off the back foot straight to extra cover where Shahid Yousuf , on for Shoaib, fields
Strauss opened the face and angled the ball down to third man
mistimed drive into the pitch
Onto the back foot and again a case of tip-and-run as the ball is dropped feet from the bat
Strauss uses his feet and slams the ball square - Mailk catches it but cannot prevent it trickling over the boundary
sound backfoot defensive shot to straight ball
again a good line and length and Bell can only play it up to mid-on
slightly short on leg stump and eased to deepish square leg where Afridi ambles in and fields. A run by consent and no-one really broke sweat
widish and there to cut but Strauss misses
Strauss angles the ball from just outside off stump to third man to bring up his 10th ODI fifty off 45 balls to a big cheer from the crowd
Naved-ul-Hasan loses his line and Bell clips him into the wide open spaces around deep midwicket
No room for Bell to do anything other than play it into the off
another one on a line and length
Bell tries to ease the ball to cover for a single but hits it too hard
worked from middle stump behind square on the leg
Strauss comes down the track and aims to smack the ball over the top but gets an all-too-obvious edge and even Akmal can't muck that one up
eased towards mid-off and Pietersen scampers throughto get off the mark straight away
flicked off one leg behind square and falls a few feet short of a diving Razzaq at backward square-leg and through him to the boundary
well placed on the leg side and despite huffing and puffing from the fielders it was a risk-free two
expansive leave by KP
exaggerated defensive shot
pushed defensive shot, comes off the toe of the bat and loops inches wide of Naved-ul-Hasan who dived well to his left
lovely clip through the gap at wide midwicket, all along the ground to the boundary
good comeback by the bowler, straight and no chance of Bell working it away
another ball that offers nothing
overpitched and driven straight, Shoaib fields but there was a run there as it was to his left hand and he was deep
angled behind square on the off but quickly pounced on
played into the covers but straight to a man. Pietersen wants to get on with this, you can see it
all wrists as he flicks it from outside off stump wide of mid-on and never anything other than a four. The kind of shot that makes we mortals envious
sublime to the ridiculous as he aims a wild heave
driven hard and Inzamam ... yes, Inzamam, dives like an Italian centre foward in the penalty box to field and sits up with a slight grin on his face
firmly driven down the ground
attempted to work the ball to third man but got in a bit of a muddle and it ended up trickling to Akmal
dug out of the blockhole and turned out to be an easy run to mid-off who has dropped back a yard or two to compensate for Pietersen's power
this time Bell's attempt to work the ball to third man is successful
played to midwicket and the optimistic shy at the stumps misses by some way but almost floors Pietersen as he makes his ground
Angled to third man ... Bell likes that shot!
good line and defended for the photographers
turned to leg but never a chance of a single
pitched up and driven to mid-off
again overpitched, turned straight to midwicket. Two moderate balls but Naved-ul-Hasan has got away with it
better line and Bell can only block it
forced onto the back foot, Pietersen started coming but quickly yelled "no, no, no" and retreated to safety
pushed to the right of a tumbling bowler but he needn't have bothered as mid-on was ambling round to cut it off
driven with no power to extra cover. A maiden from Naved-ul-Hasan
on-drives that quickly down to long-on, where it rolls and is picked up
Pietersen drives that straight back at the bowler who misses it, which is a good job as Bell was way out of his crease at the non-striker's end when the ball crashed into the stumps there
squeezed out to mid-on
deliciously cheeky late cut
strayed down leg and that's a very strong flick through midwicket and it runs away; that's Pietersen's third four
top shot, goes aerial for a two-bounce four. Really early on to that one and it's just chipped over mid-on
squeezed out to midwicket off the off stump

Pietersen tried to work that one out to the leg side but a thick outside edge flies up for a gentle catch at backward point and that's the dangerman gone. A bit of a waste of a shot, there, it probably goes without saying and Pietersen knows it: he shakes his head as he watches the replay of his demise on the big screen
off the mark immediately, guiding that away through fine leg as the ball just strays down leg. Inzamam dropped to his knees in despair at that one and Naved scratches his head, annoyed
strongly defended on the front foot
worked off the back foot into cover
defended
short and wide and that's helped into the covers for a jogged single
defended off the back foot
sails that one through on a good length, but too wide to interest the batsman
shuffles over to meet that one and it's defended firmly on the front foot
bangs that one in just in front of the toes, a touch short of yorker length and that's driven calmly to mid-on for one
defended out to mid-off
the ball drifts in there and Collingwood times that one beautifully off his toes, right out of the middle of the bat
pitches on a good length and that's defended forward
identical ball, a good line and that keeps Collingwood quiet again, he just whispers a forward defensive there
wide this time and Collingwood's quick hands whip that one deftly to the cover boundary
well waited and that ball pitches on leg where it's worked easily into midwicket
ooh! Lovely! Shoaib bangs in a bouncer which has Bell's head nearly touching his toes as he arcs sharply out of the line of that one

drives a sharp catch to point on the up. Full of length and that was a thick outside edge. Great decision from Inzamam to bring Shoaib back - it's already paid dividends, dismissing Bell just when he was showing real touch there

ooooh, attempted yorker swings back in and misses the off stump by that much and the first an astonished, worried Dalrymple knows of it is when he hears the thud in Akmal's gloves. That was hostile and the ball's reversing nicely here. Expect more fireworks
that one flies away too wide to be of interest to a relieved Dalrymple
the batsman plays it late, jamming his bat on it just in time

the most convincing shot from Dalrymple so far, turning his bat over that one and helping it to midwicket. But what a great over from Shoaib, a wicket maiden - pretty rare currency in these kind of matches of course. Top bowling and top captaincy
Collingwood lashes a cut at that one
hurries that off the backfoot out to cow corner where two fielders make a real moo of that, allowing the boundary - howler
helps that to the cover boundary
defended this time, better ball
the batsman moves his front foot across to that one which pitches outside off but chooses to leave it in the end
defends that one off the back foot. Not a bad over first up
tucked on to his back foot there to play a defensive
slower ball bounces through, low, without alarm as it's too wide to be probing
a hint of reverse swing from Shoaib and an inside edge crashes on to his pads
comes forward with a very deliberate full face of the bat and Dalrymple defends yet again

more sloppiness in the outfield and Rana Naved fails to stop that cleanly. He looks to have hurt his shoulder in the process. Inzamam and Shoaib both lean over onto their knees in frustration before realising that Rana Naved is injured. He's helped off the field where he winces and sits down behind the boundary ropes as the physio gives him some attention - but on his hip, rather than his shoulder...
defended this time
Afridi collects a return ball on the bounce
good running from England there as the ball runs into the cover
lashed off the back foot to point
lashed once more off the back foot and out to the cover boundary
defended this time
very wide one turns away from the batsman who does well to reach out and keep it down with a drive to cover
drops that a touch short and it's easily worked to square
the batsman has to put all the pace on the ball himself and that's hit into the gap on the off side
worked to square leg and that's another gently jogged single
guided down to deep fine leg
another single picked up by England there, this one into midwicket
a forward defensive to end the over
hit out to the cover boundary
tried to play a wristy drive, completely missed it and Akmal pouches that tidily
defended on the front foot
chipped up into space at mid-on, long-on rushes forward to pick it up
defended forward on the front foot
solid defence
straight and blocked. Good tight stuff
driven out easily to mid-on
cut straight to cover
messy reverse sweep which gets a run but no prized for aesthetics
driven to long-on but no run
cutto cover
much slower, turned appreciably away from the right-hander
pushed through and no more than pushed to the cover fielders
played well outside the line as he tried to push forward, loud and confident shout and looked worth a yell but perhaps his forward movement saved him
cut through the infield to the cover boundary
outside off and chipped into the leg side
straighter, on middle stump but too full to drive and he chips it to midwicket
premeditated sweep off middle stump, fine four four, no fielder within shouting distance of catching it
waited for ball and clipped it wide enough of midwicket to amble the single
again waited and turned with ease to square leg
looping one which is played to midwicket
has to reach for a sweep
waited for it and played ugly pull down the ground to mid-on
slower one and just got enough bat on it to frustrate the bowler and to get two runs on the leg
wide but pitched well up and Dalrymple could do no more than squeeze it to cover
waited for the ball and ran it down to long leg
tried the same shot but got in a bit of a muddle
another premeditated sweep which he stretched for and just about controlled
clipped off a full length safely over the infield
used feet but unable to do any more than prod to cover fielders
nurdled to the leg side
swept with venom to the square boundary - he got hold of that one and as it was slightly full he didn't have to reach for it
hit to Inzamam at short extra cover
hit harder to Inzamam at short extra cover but he's on form today
truned to the leg side, should have been one but they ran the first quickly and Yousuf misfielded, allowing them to come back for the second. Inzamam unimpressed
much the same but to the fielder
onto the back foot and punched down to mid-on
missed an attempted guide to third man but almost got an edge in the process
straight and defended as he was turned square
short and turned to deep square leg
pitched up and played down to mid-on, bringing up the 50 partnership
well worked to the deep extra cover boundary where, despite some banshee yelling from Akmal, the throw never threatens a run-out
three paces down the track but misses it and it loops off the pad into no-man's land
clipped neatly over the top and Yousuf scampers round to dive and stop the ball five yards inside the rope
driven down to Yousuf at long-on and they know he has a weak arm and they take it on successfully
smacked to the deep cover boundary
tumbling, half-stop at short mid-off enough to deter the single
proded to short extra cover
worked off his legs
short leg-side ball, ambitious hook is gloved and it loops a couple of feet over a leaping  Akmal who has no chance
turned to shortish midwicket
placed a few feet to the right of the same man and it's two once it's beaten his dive
off-balance push off the back foot to extra cover and Razzaq's throw to the bowler's end would have beaten Dalrymple by at least a yard
weak defensive prod to short extra cover
came down the track, missed, but got back before Akmal could gather it
a reverse sweep to long-off off the toe-end of the bat, hard to set a field to
straight and true
quicker ball, slightly surprised Dalrymple
expansive sweep to deep square leg, looked good but only one run.
paddled out to square where Afridi gathers it
lofted high to midwicket and that bounces just inside the rope, bringing up Dalrymple's second ODI fifty
chipped into space at mid-on
pushed on to his back foot to defend
dances down the track looking for an off-drive, gets a big inside edge into his pads instead but there's still room for a quick single
attempted yorker but that's hit out to mid-on
paddled round off his back foot, a nice little twirl, to midwicket&
strays down leg
walks into that one and chips it over to midwicket
waits for that one which turns into him; he plays against the spin and rolls his wrists over a cut
doesn't get hold of that on-drive and the ball just trickles onto the onside
dances down the track and adjusts to defend
makes room off his back foot to squirt that one into midwicket
flicked into midwicket
pulled round to the square-leg boundary
mishit a pull, in fact didn't hit it at all, and the batsmen scramble a leg-bye
comes down the pitch and stands on a leg stump line, but works the ball out through the covers in the end
gets over the ball and works it through midwicket
tries to bang that one in; it doesn't get up and that's an easy enough steer off the back foot through point
oh hello, a run-out chance there but the batsman was back in at the non-striker's end as the stumps were shied down
attempted slower ball and that's very wide indeed, oops
yorker, but that's dug out and sent on its way down to long-on
short, wide and that's helped out to the cover boundary
backs away and crashes that off the back foot with a swipe to cover, where it's cleanly picked up by Inzamam
goes over the top with a shot off the toe of the bat to bring up the hundred partnership
inswinging yorker totally cleans up Dalrymple and his leg stump was knocked right back there. Lovely
rushes at that one, trying to drive out to cover, but an inside edge flies square
squirted out to mid-on
the batsman came forward and yorked himself there with one which was full and straight and that goes through the gate to take middle stump
pitches on a good length and that's defended
brings his bat down on that one which pitches on off stump and defends it with the full face of the bat, walking into the shot
helped off the back foot into the point region
drifts on to leg and there's a strangled appeal - but it hit bat as well as missing leg
yorker, well bowled with late reverse swing, but well played too, dug out at the last minute
leg-side wide chased round by Read who was nowhere near it
short and that's dabbed off the back foot for a single to bring Collingwood back on strike
cover-driven and that brings up Collingwood's half-century from just 55 balls, with four fours
that's well picked up at cover after the ball is fair smacked there
slower ball, drizzled out to cover
short and that's lashed out to the cover boundary where the sweeper, Shoaib Malik, fluffs it. Not Pakistan's finest hour in the field, it's fair to say
lays bat on a wide yorker and a huge outside edge whisks on its merry way down through third man
ooh, not far from chopping on there as a top edge jumps over the stumps
quickly on to that one and rushes it out to the off-side boundary, just in front of point
rubbish full toss but Shoaib gets away with it as a firmly struck pull is tidily collected on the square boundary
clipped away off the legs for a single
full toss swatted straight back past the bowler
slower ball sits up and the batsmen just about make their two runs as the ball flies out to cover
right up in the blockhole and that's scrambled out by Read

slower ball, tried to work it round the corner, but got a top edge. Now, that's a smart catch by Shoaib Akhtar, running forward to cling on to that one held over his shoulder at square leg. A useful innings comes to an end and it will be up to the tail to continue the swinging now
full toss crashed out to mid-on
yorker, dug out
the batsman gives himself a bit of room, waits, and helps it off the toe-end of the bat right over through cover with some sumptuous timing. Glorious

worked out to mid-on and the batsmen look for a suicidal two. That's a good throw back in and Shoaib stands calm, at the bowler's end, whipping off the bails to leave the batsman some vital inches short. Mahmood is gone without facing a delivery
strays down leg with that one
pulled high in the air right over the bowler's head who can't make it despite a frantic chase
interesting cricket. Lewis waits and dinks that back behind point but Hafeez shells a very difficult chance indeed, wide to his left. Good work to stop the runs, all the same
top shot! Have some of that! The batsman rushes that back over Shoaib's head and way, way over to long-off for a one-bounce four. A full bloodied swing and gets the reward
played off the back foot into cover

lovely stuff from the batsman, dire stuff from the fielder. Lewis square drives that with some force but Afridi tries to stop the ball with his foot - not in the textbook, of course - and though he gets a toe to it, it runs over the rope
much better fielding and takes the catch at long-on, sliced away by Lewis and that's well held after an initial misjudgement, which has Shoaib Malik scrambling backwards to take that over his head
whipped out on the on-side
driven uppishly but safely to the long-on region
comes down the wicket and has a whoosh, but misses that completely

inn2.comm: widish, swinging away from the batsman. He got away with that as it should have been called, and he gives a grin to the umpire as he walks back past him
turned Shoaib square and the ball squirted off the edge to third man
defended, a fairly nondescript ball but the slips chirp and clap nevertheless
again squeezed rather than played behind square on the leg
left alone but it moved slightly in to the batsman, but nowhere nearly enough to cause any serious alarms
loose drive to another full-length ball wide of off stump which moved away off the pitch  and it goes at head height straight to Paul Collingwood at cover who gleefully catches it
given room and driven airily but safely to wide third man where Mahmood makes a good one-handed pick-up on the rope
fullish and blocked
leg side, struck Hafeez on the pads and rolled to Read
driven straight past Broad and a scampered single to add to the no-ball. Broad looks perplexed with the umpire's decision but the TV replay shows he was well over the line
too wide but left alone
Younis in the air when he plays that shot, inside edge into his body and the ball squirts past his stumps. It could have gone anywhere
shaped to cut but doesn't get hold of it
in the groove and defended
Hafeez hurried on the back foot and can do no more than defend
jabbed to mid-on but not a sniff of a run
lifts outside off stump and Hafeez plays and misses as it gets big on him
unconvincing attempted drive off the back foot flies over the slips. Safe but Lewis is posing Hafeez problems
end of a good over as again Lewis gives no room for Younis to play a shot
fast, with bounce, but the radar needs adjusting as it flew down the leg side
drive, slightly off balance as he was leaning back, and it goes gently to mid-off
once again Hafeez slashes at one and it shoots inches past a diving, airbourne Strauss at gully
Younis doesn't time an attempted drive
steered to cover. Younis not being given any width to unleash his weaponery
inside edge which Younis knew little about and he is grateful that it trundled safely square on the leg
overpitched and driven with authority through mid-on
back to the edge as Younis gets it down to third man with no conviction
no chance of anything as Lewis in the groove
Hafeez cramped for room and hurried
good - straight and fast, and a textbook defensive stroke
where on earth did that come from!  Hafeez takes two paces to meet the ball and launches it several rows back into the crowd
Lewis rattled, overpitches on leg stump and Hafeez nonchalantly flicks it over midwicket for another four
not to be outdone, Younis leans back and hammers the ball through the covers. That's 14 off three deliveries
leg side, but Younis misses an attempted flick over the infield

strange run given that England were looking rattled after the last few deliveries  ... played into the packed off side and Strauss races in and throws while diving, his direct hit leaves Hafeez, who hesitated at the start, inches short. It went to the third umpire and at the time it looked as if Hafeez might have made it, but the replays were clear
jagged back in and struck Yousuf on the pads. No chance of an appeal as it was well outside the line
cautiously defended
he thought about playing it but pulled out of the shot in good time
dribbled into the leg-side field
steered to cover
breaks the stranglehold by angling the ball down to third man
good, fast ball which Yousuf can do no more than keep out
slightly loose and over flamboyant drive which goes almost nowhere
a better-looking stroke but no more productive
steered towards third man but Trescothick makes a diving stop at very wide slip/very fine gully (take your pick)
wide and slashed straight to cover where ot bounces kindly to Pietersen who then skies at the bowler's end and causes Yousuf to scamper in a rather undignified manner
another attempted drive and once again not timed
good delivery -  Yousuf not being given a chance to get off the mark
defended with bat behind the pad and the ball bobbles up and trickles to the slip area
Yousuf forced onto the back foot and, again, can only keep it out
beats the outside edge, massive shout from bowler and keeper - and others in no position to see - but no joy and it looks as if Billy Doctrove was right&
Yousuf off the mark with an easy single
another one where Younis had to settle for keeping it out. Lewis turns and has a quiet word with the umpire
messy, rolls safely past stumps and wide enough to allow the run
much more convincing, Braod gives Younis too much width and he unleashes a crisp drive which penetrates the fielders and lollops off to the rope
short, pulled from outside off stump with real venom and it bounces inches short of the midwicket boundary. Perhaps England should not upset him any more
cracked into the off but straight to Collingwood
slower ball which Younis steers safely into the off
dinked to midwicket and a cheeky single is scampered through
pushed out on the off side
this time that goes to mid-on
carved through cover, lovely
pushed right up there and that's defended
on the button and that's another defensive to finish a tidy over from Lewis
ooh, thwack. That's a huge pull shot, with a lovely roll of the wrists right over that one and that rockets away. Cracker
dinked into cover
pushed right up there and that's defended this time, a better ball
lovely shot off the backfoot - really opened his arms and lashed that one away behind point. Beautiful
defended into cover
played off the back foot down to wide third man
defended off the back foot
worked off the back foot to point
cracking shot back over his head with a thumping straight drive
chipped into midwicket - but apparently off the pads
pushed into midwicket
defended forward
overstepped no-ball
dabbed to mid off
pushed up there and defended
helped into cover
sweetly timed through mid-on with a lovely on-drive
defended again
tried to on-drive again, but it's not timed this time
improvised whip off the front foot through square, lovely shot! (even if it's just one run)
dropped a touch short but that's just helped to point where it's picked up and winged back in, side-arm and casual, by Pietersen
worked off the legs to square
defended
straight drive back down the ground and Billy Doctrove has to jump over that one as he's completely nutmegged
good work on the point boundary by Broad who cuts off the four
defended
lovely shot, well timed off the hips and that's whipped round through fine leg. Super. Mahmood roars his annoyance at dropping that one short
bangs that in, great reply and that rears off a length, forcing Yousuf to defend, late, away from his face. That's the spirit
on a length and that's defended
hit out to point
defended first up
very wide down leg
defended
down leg again and that's another frankly rubbish wide

yet another wide - dross
defended
easy single to mid-on

the batsmen rush through a single

defended

solid defensive block

much tigther line

lunging forward defensive shot

tamer end to the over

and that's a quick single. Pakistan are looking well set here for the charge

a quiet defensive to finish that over
on the money there and that's easily defended
late cut to third man
slower ball, dug out
defended

driven to cover
drops that short and it's chipped over the bowler's head but not near enough the bowler

whipped off the legs
